 JOHANNESBURG - As interviews for new SABC board members began wrapping up on Friday, Judge Chris Greenland provided some light-hearted humour.Seventy-four-year old Greenland was the first candidate to face MPs and he dismissed suggestions his age may affect his performance, if chosen for the position.He even challenged EFF MP, Mbuyiseni Ndlozi, to a golf match.RECORDED: MPs grill candidates for new SABC boardBut it was the last part of his interview that was rather amusing.When asked by EFF MP Mbuyiseni Ndlozi to name his favourite TV show on SABC, he responded Checkpoint.Ndlozi then corrected Greenland. "Checkpoint is on eNCA, judge," said Ndlozi.eNCA